quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  32,1,"Alif-Lam-Meem. (Alphabets of the Arabic language – Allah and to whomever He reveals, know their precise meanings.)"
  32,2,"The revelation of the Book is, without doubt, from the Lord Of The Creation."
  32,3,"What! They dare say that, “He has fabricated it”? In fact it is the Truth from your Lord, in order that you warn a nation towards whom no Herald of Warning came before you, in the hope of their attaining guidance."
  32,4,"It is Allah Who created the heavens and the earth, and all what is between them, in six days, then (befitting His Majesty) established Himself over the Throne (of control); leaving Allah, there is neither a friend nor an intercessor for you; so do you not ponder?"
  32,5,"He plans (all) the job(s) from the heaven to the earth – then it will return to Him on the Day which amounts to a thousand years in your count."
  32,6,"This is the All Knowing – of all the hidden and the visible, the Most Honourable, the Most Merciful."
  32,7,"The One Who created all things excellent, and Who initiated the creation of man from clay."
  32,8,"Then kept his posterity with a part of an abject fluid."
  32,9,"Then made him proper and blew into him a spirit from Him, and bestowed ears and eyes and hearts to you; very little thanks do you offer!"
  32,10,"And they said, “When we have mingled into the earth, will we be created again?”; in fact they disbelieve in the meeting with their Lord."
  32,11,"Proclaim, “The angel of death, who is appointed over you, causes you to die and then towards your Lord you will return.”"
